REVIEWS

PHYSIOLOGY 28: 172–189, 2013; doi:10.1152/physiol.00055.2012

Transduction of Voltage and Ca2؉ Signals by Slo1 BK Channels
Large-conductance Ca2ϩ- and voltage-gated Kϩ channels are activated by an increase in intracellular Ca2ϩ concentration and/or depolarization. The channel activation mechanism is well described by an allosteric model encompassing the gate, voltage sensors, and Ca2ϩ sensors, and the model is an excellent

T. Hoshi,1 A. Pantazis,2 and R. Olcese2,3,4
